text: Governor Hassan Proposes Balanced Budget to Continue Building a More Innovative Economic Future http://t.co/Dvl80bY648
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “Over the last two years, we have proven that by working across party lines we can make significant progress.”
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “There are additional investments that we may want to make… but the revenue isn’t there to responsibly do those things in this budget.”
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “More efficient, more competitive and more successful economically.” (2/2)
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “What we have done in this budget is make the strategic investments that we can afford to help make New Hampshire…” (1/2)
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “And we must never forget how important it is to the lives of our people.” (2/2)
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “The work that state government does must be done efficiently, thoughtfully and frugally…” (1/2)
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “These are priorities that must be met…if we want to expand opportunity & build a more innovative economic future.”
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “And we know that young people want affordable higher education & modern transportation options.”
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “We know that our families are counting on safe communities, good schools & a high quality of life.”
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “But to truly address the public safety needs of our state, we must also renew our focus on the corrections system.”
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “This budget uses those funds to expand efficiency and renewable energy projects.” (2/2)
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “The RGGI and the REF are critical to encouraging energy efficiency & diversification through our growing clean energy sector.” (1/2)
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “That is why this budget will allow DRED to develop a workforce recruitment strategy.” (3/3)
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “But we also need to once again encourage more young people from other states to choose NH…” (2/3)
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “We need to keep more of our young people here in NH…” (1/3)
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “Our capital budget includes 4 million dollars for environmental & engineering assessment that this vital project requires to move forward.”
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “Commuter rail will build on our many advantages and help set the stage for a new generation of economic growth.”
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “We know that a modern, safe transportation infrastructure is critical to the success of our people and businesses.”
name: Maggie Hassan

text: In #NHSOTS, Gov. Hassan Calls for Continued Bipartisanship to Strengthen Middle Class and Accelerate Economic Growth http://t.co/mgCkqxE2Cq
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "Because, for the State of New Hampshire, the best way forward is always through." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "We must continue to prove the strength of our democracy by working through our challenges together." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "I like to say that, in NH, we do democracy better than anyplace else." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "But what matters – to our economy, to our businesses, to the people of our state – is what we do after we argue." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "I ask the legislature to heed Becky’s call and pass this bill, pass “Joshua’s Law,” in memory of her beautiful son." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "establishing a crime of domestic violence... will help law enforcement and prosecutors better identify and stop repeat abusers." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "...with information about individuals who should not be sold a firearm due to serious mental illness." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "One pressing public safety issue is the fact that NH does not provide the current background check system..." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "But we know that our work is never complete, that we can always make our communities safer and stronger." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "And maintaining NH’s distinction as one of the safest states in the nation is our most important responsibility." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "I do not believe that a young person with a substance problem should end up in jail, prison or with a criminal record..." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "We do need to thoughtfully consider our current policies toward substance abuse to refocus on treatment." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "We must focus on improving access to treatment for all substances, especially among our young people." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "For those w/ mental health needs & for all patients, providers need to offer the right care, at the right time, in the right place."#NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "...to effectively treat those with mental illness, just as they treat others with chronic conditions." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "But we must also work to fully integrate these community-based services into our larger health care system..." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "I encourage the full legislature to... reinforce our commitment to a revitalized community-based mental health system." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "This is a challenge facing our health care providers, police officers, and communities across the state..." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "...and they must be able to access that care before they reach the point of crisis." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "People with mental illness are our friends, our family members, our neighbors who are simply in need of appropriate care..." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: “…Now let’s get this done.” #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "I thank members of both parties, from both the House and the Senate, for their steadfast commitment to reaching a compromise..." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "It’s clear that we can work through this together & help working people access critical health coverage." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "Moving forward with health care expansion is supported by hospitals, providers, businesses, and the people of NH." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "Right now, we have an opportunity to work through another long-standing issue – healthcare costs and access." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "...and we can do it w/o sacrificing the scenic views and beautiful natural resources that drive our economy and define us..." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "By working together, we can take steps to build a stronger, more affordable energy future..." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "Expanding natural gas pipeline capacity for our region is one way to reduce energy costs in NH." #NHSOTS

name: Maggie Hassan

text: "Job-creating businesses need to know that NH’s small, accessible & nimble government will continue to be responsive to their needs."#NHSOTS

text: "...directly with classes at local schools, building relationships that can lead to a stronger workforce pipeline." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "I have asked Commissioner Jeff Rose and DRED to lead a new effort this year to partner manufacturing companies..." #NHSOTS

name: Maggie Hassan

text: "Our schools need to provide an even more rigorous STEM education that our businesses believe in..." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "For our students to succeed, we must work together to ensure that communities are able to implement..." #NHSOTS

text: "We have heard from our businesses that we still have work to do to ensure that we have a workforce that can compete in the future." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "...and made it possible for our universities and community colleges to freeze in-state tuition." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "We took an important step in that effort working together through the budget. We restored higher education funding..." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "To build an even stronger workforce, we must keep more of our young people here in NH." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "We can work our way through to compromise, and through compromise to progress for our economy and our people." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "We must keep our state and our economy moving forward, and for NH, the best way forward is always through." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "We face long-standing challenges – from education to infrastructure to energy to health care.” #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "NH remains one of the safest, healthiest and most livable states in the nation – and the best place to raise a family." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "With nearly unanimous support from those in this historic chamber, we enacted the most bipartisan budget in more than a decade." #NHSOTS
name: Maggie Hassan

text: "We have demonstrated that the traditions of hard work, collaboration, and bipartisan problem-solving have returned to Concord." #NHSOTS

text: "In NH, we have worked together to support middle class families, to help innovative businesses thrive and to grow our economy." #NHSOTS
